    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-12T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-12T07:00:00-05:00" n="126"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 793.94/293.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extracts.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-12T20:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1915—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At Saturday’s conference the Chinese endeavored to secure a definite acceptance
                    of concessions which they have made in regard to Manchuria but the Japanese
                    Minister stated that he had not yet received instructions authorizing him to
                    make, final settlement. He <pb facs="0242" n="126" xml:id="pg_126"/> then
                    attempted to discuss Articles 4, 5, and 6 of Group V. The Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs insisted that he could not consider these demands in principle since
                    they conflict with China’s sovereignty and treaty obligations. The Japanese
                    Minister thereupon stated that he could not see the force of these arguments in
                    view of what the Chinese had already found it possible to grant in
                    Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
